From: Hadron Port <hadron@localhost>
Date: 2026-01-01
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] vulkan/wsi: connect to Hadron Wayland compositor

The Wayland WSI creates a connection to $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/wayland-0.
On Hadron, XDG_RUNTIME_DIR defaults to /run if the env var is unset.
This patch adds a fallback so the WSI connects successfully without
requiring the env var to be set explicitly.

diff --git a/src/vulkan/wsi/wsi_common_wayland.c b/src/vulkan/wsi/wsi_common_wayland.c
--- a/src/vulkan/wsi/wsi_common_wayland.c
+++ b/src/vulkan/wsi/wsi_common_wayland.c
@@ -79,6 +79,10 @@ wsi_wl_display_init(struct wsi_wl_display *display, ...)
 {
+#if DETECT_OS_HADRON
+   /* On Hadron, XDG_RUNTIME_DIR defaults to /run */
+   if (!getenv("XDG_RUNTIME_DIR"))
+      setenv("XDG_RUNTIME_DIR", "/run", 0);
+#endif
+
    /* ... existing connection logic unchanged ... */
 }
